# =========================================================================
#  Easy Rigify — .gitignore
#  Keeps the repo to the shippable addon + crypto build source + CI.
#  Everything heavy (datasets, backups, .blend scenes, training checkpoints)
#  and everything secret (plaintext models/weights) stays OUT of git.
# =========================================================================

# ---- Python / OS / editor noise ----
# NOTE: intentionally *.pyc / *.pyo only (NOT the *.py[cod] shorthand) — that
# bracket pattern also matches *.pyd, which is exactly the compiled Windows
# crypto binary this repo needs to ship (native/_ercrypto_win_amd64.pyd). It
# silently ate that file from both the first local commit and CI's commit-back
# step. Never use *.py[cod] in this repo.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp

# ---- Blender assets / packaged builds (multi-GB) ----
*.blend
*.blend1
*.zip

# ---- Stale backups / build intermediates ----
*.bak
*.bak_*
*.rmodel.bak*
/dev/native/build/

# ---- Model / weight files = IP, never on GitHub ----
*.pt          # PyTorch training checkpoints
*.onnx        # plaintext models
*.pth

# ---- ALL of dev/ is local tooling & datasets EXCEPT the crypto build source
#      and the Lite build script (both are ship recipes — losing them means an
#      edition can't be rebuilt) ----
/dev/*
!/dev/native/
!/dev/build_lite.py
!/dev/GAME_EXPORT_DESIGN.md
/dev/native/_build/
/dev/native/_rmodel_backup_v1/

# ---- Other multi-GB dirs at the repo root ----
/Backup/
/face_dataset/
/debug_face_infer/

# NOTE: these ARE committed on purpose —
#   models/*.rmodel      (ENCRYPTED, needed to ship)
#   native/_ercrypto_*   (compiled crypto binaries, committed by CI)
#   dev/native/*.c,*.py  (crypto build source — THIS IS WHY THE REPO MUST BE PRIVATE)
#   dev/build_lite.py    (builds the Lite edition — see section 9.1 of DOCUMENTATION.txt)
#   dev/GAME_EXPORT_DESIGN.md  (game-engine export design + bug post-mortem)
#   wheels/*.whl         (bundled onnxruntime + Pillow, ~153MB — see
#                          blender_manifest.toml `wheels=` and dev/native/download_wheels.py)
